00:22:38,610 --> 00:22:40,050
She is really pretty.

263
00:22:40,090 --> 00:22:42,390
What did you see? Notting Hill?

264
00:22:42,390 --> 00:22:44,570
No. Stepmom.

265
00:22:45,290 --> 00:22:47,210
I didn't watch that movie.

266
00:22:48,170 --> 00:22:52,130
It's just a story about a mom who raises kids she didn't give birth to.

267
00:22:53,550 --> 00:22:55,590
She was a stepmom.

268
00:22:55,610 --> 00:22:57,890
She didn't even give birth to them.

269
00:22:59,610 --> 00:23:03,730
Definitely, Julia Roberts is beautiful.

270
00:23:25,010 --> 00:23:27,130
But this day, I did a different surgery.

271
00:23:27,130 --> 00:23:29,490
I really hate it.

272
00:23:29,970 --> 00:23:32,370
Where exactly did she put her maturity that comes with age?

273
00:23:32,370 --> 00:23:35,350
A woman who found love so she left her son,

274
00:23:35,370 --> 00:23:40,470
how can she call every time she gets in trouble to cry and whine? I swear she is selfish.

275
00:23:40,510 --> 00:23:43,230
People are normally selfish.

276
00:23:44,890 --> 00:23:46,930
Still, she shouldn't do it to her child.

277
00:23:46,970 --> 00:23:48,210
Noona,

278
00:23:48,710 --> 00:23:50,970
she is my mom.

279
00:23:50,970 --> 00:23:52,350
That's right.

280
00:23:53,130 --> 00:23:56,570
Thanks to your great mom you are in this state.

281
00:23:56,610 --> 00:23:59,890
At your age, you haven't even had a proper passionate love life.

282
00:23:59,890 --> 00:24:02,850
And then you get dumped because you're so ambivalent.

283
00:24:02,890 --> 00:24:04,590
Oh man.

284
00:24:04,590 --> 00:24:06,930
I don't think you're in a position to worry about someone else.

285
00:24:06,970 --> 00:24:09,430
What about your public display of your taste for idols?

286
00:24:09,450 --> 00:24:12,470
Others would perceive it as perverted.

287
00:24:12,510 --> 00:24:15,270
Hey, where are you fanning the sparks?

288
00:24:15,310 --> 00:24:18,550
Do you know how comfortable it is dating idols?

289
00:24:18,570 --> 00:24:19,970
Is it comfortable?

290
00:24:20,470 --> 00:24:23,150
I can love them as much as I want.

291
00:24:23,190 --> 00:24:25,730
They just say thank you every now and then for loving them.

292
00:24:25,730 --> 00:24:29,250
I can love them with my whole heart, and not worry about getting hurt.

293
00:24:29,730 --> 00:24:31,670
Hey, I'm happy.

294
00:24:32,190 --> 00:24:35,550
At this age giving, receiving, pushing, pulling, crying, screaming, oh!

295
00:24:35,550 --> 00:24:37,670
I'm tired just thinking about it.

296
00:24:39,150 --> 00:24:44,010
I think I'm the only one who is exhausted with Ms. Choi's love for idols.

297
00:24:44,010 --> 00:24:48,270
What have you done to be tired about? What is there? Huh?

298
00:24:52,230 --> 00:24:54,370
Just like they say, like father, like son.

299
00:24:54,370 --> 00:24:58,310
Your father always sided with your mother too,

300
00:24:58,370 --> 00:25:01,130
even though I never could understand.

301
00:25:12,390 --> 00:25:14,290
Pancakes!

302
00:25:14,310 --> 00:25:16,390
Here, here, here.

303
00:25:22,690 --> 00:25:24,210
Wait!

304
00:25:25,290 --> 00:25:26,950
Bring Won over.

305
00:25:26,950 --> 00:25:29,690
Let him be alone tonight.

306
00:25:29,690 --> 00:25:31,670
You're taking care of Won and everything.

307
00:25:31,710 --> 00:25:34,710
Won likes pancakes more than you.

308
00:25:34,710 --> 00:25:41,550
And, I like Won, who makes the person who cooked it feel good by eating so deliciously, the best!

309
00:25:41,550 --> 00:25:44,210
Leave some for him and pack it.

310
00:25:44,210 --> 00:25:50,110
But, are eating together at one table and eating separately the same?

311
00:25:50,110 --> 00:25:54,150
Pay some attention to your actual son who is eating with you.

312
00:25:55,170 --> 00:25:59,850
Son, isn't paying less attention to you better?

313
00:25:59,850 --> 00:26:02,430
What happened to the resume you submitted to the company?

314
00:26:02,470 --> 00:26:04,970
You said you were going to get a part-time job to make your own allowance. Why aren't you doing it?

315
00:26:04,970 --> 00:26:07,650
You said you would go to a Chinese academy in the morning, and also attend grad school.

316
00:26:07,650 --> 00:26:10,590
Stop it! Don't pay attention. Act like I'm not here.

317
00:26:10,590 --> 00:26:12,250
I put your allowance on top of your desk.

318
00:26:12,270 --> 00:26:13,770
I put some on there too.

319
00:26:13,770 --> 00:26:16,070
Oh? Also, some of my precious cash—

320
00:26:16,730 --> 00:26:19,250
Hey, punk! Return that allowance that's as precious as my blood!

321
00:26:19,270 --> 00:26:20,450
Where am I returning it?

322
00:26:20,450 --> 00:26:23,910
Jowoon Bank, 360238402.

323
00:26:23,910 --> 00:26:25,430
Dad.

324
00:26:25,430 --> 00:26:26,610
Ah, my son.

325
00:26:41,720 --> 00:26:45,160
♬  If I need you ♬

326
00:26:45,170 --> 00:26:48,410
♬ Would you come tome  ♬

327
00:26:48,450 --> 00:26:53,970
♬ Would you come to me and hold me to ease my pain.  ♬

328
00:26:57,870 --> 00:27:01,730
Am I prettier, or is Julia Roberts prettier?
♬ If you needed me, I would come to you ♬

329
00:27:02,450 --> 00:27:03,470
What?

330
00:27:03,490 --> 00:27:06,810
Am I prettier or is Julia Roberts prettier?
♬  I would swim the sea  ♬

331
00:27:07,590 --> 00:27:09,330
Julia Roberts.
♬   to ease your pain. ♬

332
00:27:09,830 --> 00:27:14,970
Hey! How great would it be if you just told your friend that she is prettier?!
♬  Well the night's so long ♬

333
00:27:14,970 --> 00:27:16,790
You win with age.

334
00:27:16,790 --> 00:27:20,430
Forget it, you cheapskate. I'm not playing with you.
♬  and the mornng's born♬

335
00:27:20,430 --> 00:27:24,190
♬  And the morning's born with lights of love♬

336
00:27:24,190 --> 00:27:26,270
Hey, where did you go?

337
00:27:26,330 --> 00:27:30,470
Where would I go? I just laid down
