00:27:44,730 --> 00:27:47,930
♬  Would you come to me? ♬

344
00:27:47,930 --> 00:27:55,400
♬ Would you come to me, holding me to ease my pain?♬

345
00:28:03,170 --> 00:28:05,090
Team leader...

346
00:28:05,090 --> 00:28:06,610
Why are you here?

347
00:28:06,610 --> 00:28:09,530
You didn't go for the PPL (product placement) ad shoot?

348
00:28:09,530 --> 00:28:11,750
The thing is...

349
00:28:11,750 --> 00:28:14,790
I got the wrong size,

350
00:28:14,790 --> 00:28:18,550
so I couldn't even put it on the model. What do I do?

351
00:28:18,550 --> 00:28:20,510
What?! Are you crazy?!

352
00:28:20,510 --> 00:28:22,270
So how can you just come back here?!

353
00:28:22,270 --> 00:28:25,710
I told you yesterday to check the item number and size!

354
00:28:27,050 --> 00:28:30,670
- The filming site is in Cheongdam-dong, right?
- Yes.

355
00:28:30,670 --> 00:28:33,670
Yes, manager. It's Oh Ha Na from the headquarter's marketing team.

356
00:28:33,710 --> 00:28:36,590
I was wondering if you have in stock a size 240 of the T1715 with the sleeve on—

357
00:28:36,590 --> 00:28:38,730
You're always a step behind.

358
00:28:38,750 --> 00:28:42,830
They're shooting well while wearing M shoes.

359
00:28:46,210 --> 00:28:50,010
There's a tolerance for mistakes that can be made. But what?

360
00:28:50,010 --> 00:28:52,310
A size mistake?

361
00:28:52,310 --> 00:28:55,510
Oh, how embarrassing. How could you not check that, Team Leader Oh?

362
00:28:55,510 --> 00:28:57,730
- I'm sorry.
- You're sorry.

363
00:28:57,730 --> 00:29:00,670
Are those words something that should even come out of your mouth as a Team Leader?!

364
00:29:00,670 --> 00:29:05,110
It was my fault, Director. Team Leader had told me many times to check it, but I...

365
00:29:05,130 --> 00:29:06,490
I...

366
00:29:06,490 --> 00:29:09,170
What are you doing right now? Wipe your tears, won't you?

367
00:29:09,170 --> 00:29:11,050
This is not something that Eun Jung should be punished over.

368
00:29:11,070 --> 00:29:14,330
An unexpected situation can rise anytime during work.

369
00:29:14,350 --> 00:29:18,350
Being able to foresee this kind of situation and control it is the Team Leader's responsibility!

370
00:29:18,390 --> 00:29:21,010
Why else would you have a higher salary than Eun Jung?

371
00:29:21,030 --> 00:29:22,430
As high as your salary is should be—

372
00:29:22,450 --> 00:29:26,690
There was a time when tears were also my weapon.

373
00:29:26,690 --> 00:29:30,670
However to the present me, who is 34 and the team leader,

374
00:29:30,690 --> 00:29:32,730
tears are incompetence

375
00:29:32,750 --> 00:29:35,650
and reasons are just excuses.

376
00:29:35,690 --> 00:29:38,550
Right now what I need is

377
00:29:38,570 --> 00:29:41,730
the ability to stick it out.

378
00:29:55,590 --> 00:29:57,210
Non-employees are prohibited entry here.

379
00:29:57,210 --> 00:29:59,410
They let me in, though.

380
00:30:04,370 --> 00:30:07,590
Are we that close for you to come looking for me out of the blue?

381
00:30:07,610 --> 00:30:10,970
It's a relationship that warrants our meeting, whether it is a good relationship

382
00:30:10,970 --> 00:30:12,710
or not.

383
00:30:13,830 --> 00:30:16,150
There is no reason for me to meet you.

384
00:30:18,610 --> 00:30:20,510
Oh Ha Na. You have to become more fit. It's no fun playing with someone so unfit.

385
00:30:20,510 --> 00:30:22,370
I just wanted to confirm one thing.

386
00:30:22,370 --> 00:30:26,390
You and Ha Na are still just friends, right?

387
00:30:27,010 --> 00:30:29,430
Why do I have to tell those things to you?

388
00:30:29,470 --> 00:30:32,610
What I know is that the two of you do not have that kind of relationship.

389
00:30:33,210 --> 00:30:36,610
It means that I do not have to say those things to you.

390
00:30:37,570 --> 00:30:40,810
Well, even if I don't exactly hear the answer,

391
00:30:44,390 --> 00:30:46,970
I got the gist.

392
00:30:49,870 --> 00:30:52,410
Don't shake Ha Na.

393
00:30:53,830 --> 00:30:56,830
Shaking her is my decision. Her wavering,

394
00:30:57,550 --> 00:31:00,110
isn't that Oh Ha Na's decision?

395
00:31:00,750 --> 00:31:03,730
Then stopping you, is that my decision?

396
00:31:04,270 --> 00:31:05,890
Listen closely, Cha Seo Hoo.

397
00:31:05,910 --> 00:31:10,230
I won't let Ha Na waver because of a guy like you ever again.

398
00:31:12,990 --> 00:31:15,310
And you have the right to do that?

399
00:31:15,310 --> 00:31:19,070
I really hate being blocked by someone who has no right to do so.

400
00:31:19,830 --> 00:31:21,830
That's why I came. But

401
00:31:21,850 --> 00:31:23,830
I guess

402
00:31:24,630 --> 00:31:27,510
we'll see what happens again.

403
00:31:56,010 --> 00:31:57,490
What is this?

404
00:31:57,490 --> 00:31:58,750
Is it really for me?

405
00:31:58,750 --> 00:32:00,730
Yes, a delivery came in.

406
00:32:00,730 --> 00:32:03,570
Who sent it? Have you checked?

407
00:32:03,570 --> 00:32:06,030
I don't know about that.

408
00:32:06,030 --> 00:32:07,650
Really?

409
00:32:24,770 --> 00:32:27,210
Who sent this?

410
00:32:32,870 --> 00:32:34,380
Should we go eat spicy rice cakes?

411
00:32:34,380 --> 00:32:38,240
No... But can't you do something about this?

412
00:32:41,690 --> 00:32:44,670
Someone sent it to your company anonymously?

413
00:32:44,670 --> 00:32:50,150
Yeah, I asked the delivery guy but got nothing.

414
00:32:51,290 --> 00:32:54,030
- Don't bring it home.
- Why not?

415
00:32:54,030 --> 00:32:56,340
Why would you bring it home when you don't know who sent it?

416
00:32:56,340 --> 00:32:59,320
Because it was sent to my work, for me.

417
00:32:59,320 --> 00:33:04,610
Maybe it's someone who has a grudge against you like your co-workers?

418
00:33:04,610 --> 00:33:08,070
They might have placed a bomb or something inside.

419
00:33:10,670 --> 00:33:15,510
You're crazy. It's my first time receiving such a large doll as a gift.

420
00:33:15,510 --> 00:33:17,670
I'm in a good mood.

421
00:33:21,970 --> 00:33:25,070
I'll just buy you a new one that's safe.

422
00:33:25,070 --> 00:33:29,100
Forget it. You're saying anything just because you don't want to carry it.

423
00:33:29,100 --> 00:33:31,540
Let's go home.

424
00:33:33,980 --> 00:33:36,020
Let's not go home.

425
00:33:37,660 --> 00:33:40,540
What are you talking about? Why shouldn't I go home?

426
00:33:40,540 --> 00:33:44,940
Let's stay together for a bit more, and go home when it's late at night.

427
00:33:48,580 --> 00:33:51,700
The channel of movement of career women on a weekday night

428
00:33:51,700 --> 00:33:54,680
has to be short and close to their home.

429
00:34:04,370 --> 00:34:07,970
Admit it now, you are 34 years old and out of shape.

430
00:34:08,710 --> 00:34:11,970
Alright. I admit it. I admit it!

431
00:34:11,970 --> 00:34:16,130
Ahhh, I'm really tired!

432
00:34:26,730 --> 00:34:28,490
Here.

433
00:34:29,450 --> 00:34:31,330
Aigoo.

434
00:34:34,690 --> 00:34:36,170
Go inside.

435
00:34:36,170 --> 00:34:39,420
Sorry. I'll hang out with you more next time.

436
00:34:45,880 --> 00:34:49,120
I really don't want to go to work tomorrow.

437
00:35:10,360 --> 00:35:12,220
Ehhh?

438
00:35:18,010 --> 00:35:21,290
Your face is scarier than the doll's face.

439
00:35:21,290 --> 00:35:25,850
Daughter, come home early and rest.

440
00:35:25,850 --> 00:35:27,490
I'm tired.

441
00:35:27,490 --> 00:35:28,970
Quickly go upstairs and sleep.

442
00:35:28,970 --> 00:35:29,790
What about Dad?

443
00:35:29,790 --> 00:35:35,930
He went to sleep early. He has to go to a local mall early tomorrow morning.

444
00:35:38,190 --> 00:35:42,850
Aigoo. She's becoming more and more ridiculous.

445
00:35:42,850 --> 00:35:46,170
I really don't think the doll fits you, Ha Na.

446
00:35:46,170 --> 00:35:49,510
It seems like you're making frantic efforts to become younger!

447
00:35:49,510 --> 00:35:51,580
Ha Na's back?

448
00:35:55,400 --> 00:35:57,980
She must be tired.

449
00:35:57,980 --> 00:36:01,180
It is hard working under other people to make a living.

450
00:36:01,180 --> 00:36:04,940
She came home with a huge bunny doll she got from somewhere.

451
00:36:04,940 --> 00:36:07,860
At her age, there's no way she would have received a doll as a present.

452
00:36:07,860 --> 00:36:11,160
Is she saying she won't get married, but raise that doll as she grows old instead?

453
00:36:11,160 --> 00:36:13,180
After what happened with Seo Hoo...

454
00:36:13,180 --> 00:36:18,340
Seeing her start to date Ho Joon, I thought it was getting better, but...

455
00:36:18,340 --> 00:36:21,080
Why are you bringing that bastard up?

456
00:36:21,080 --> 00:36:23,550
It's because it's so unfortunate.

457
00:36:23,550 --> 00:36:26,730
Since she's like this during such a good age.

458
00:36:26,730 --> 00:36:30,410
What's so unfortunate? She's doing what she wants to do and living well. It's good.

459
00:36:30,410 --> 00:36:32,550
I'm going to live with her forever!

460
00:36:32,550 --> 00:36:36,830
Have a great time with your daughter then! I'm not doing that, so good luck with that!

461
00:36:55,810 --> 00:37:01,050
Maybe it's someone who has a grudge against you like your co-workers?

462
00:37:01,050 --> 00:37:04,390
There might be some sort of bomb or something in there.

463
00:37:09,410 --> 00:37:16,450
Timing and Subtitles brought to you by The Timeless Lovers @ Viki

464
00:37:36,240 --> 00:37:38,460
Bunny is all-clear!

465
00:37:58,470 --> 00:38:04,100
Woo Hyun, I'm Noona Mi Hyang. Let's do well from now on.

466
00:38:06,120 --> 00:38:07,780
Oh? Oh my, thank you.

467
00:38:07,780 --> 00:38:10,380
You are getting off in the afternoon, right?

468
00:38:10,380 --> 00:38:12,040
Yes. But why?

469
00:38:12,040 --> 00:38:16,650
Me too. Do you have any plans?

470
00:38:16,650 --> 00:38:18,130
If you're treating, then sure!

471
00:38:18,130 --> 00:38:20,870
Then I can choose the location, right?

472
00:38:20,870 --> 00:38:22,430
Yeah.

473
00:38:30,820 --> 00:38:33,520
Wow, you didn't have to go this far.

474
00:38:33,520 --> 00:38:38,160
Wow! How did you know my preferences?

475
00:38:39,560 --> 00:38:42,760
I gathered some information to get some brownie points from you.

476
00:38:42,760 --> 00:38:46,040
Well, your real goal may not be me...

477
00:38:46,040 --> 00:38:48,540
In any case, cheers!

478
00:38:53,220 --> 00:38:55,840
So what does Oppa Won like?

479
00:38:55,840 --> 00:39:01,720
For example, the kind of girls he likes, his hobbies, or any certain abilities?

480
00:39:05,450 --> 00:39:07,070
You won't like the answer though.

481
00:39:07,070 --> 00:39:09,330
What? Why not?

482
00:39:09,330 --> 00:39:15,070
I haven't heard him talk about anything about girls besides Ha Na.

483
00:39:15,070 --> 00:39:17,790
He's not picky about food, but...

484
00:39:17,790 --> 00:39:20,810
he likes the food that Ha Na's mother makes for him the best.

485
00:39:20,810 --> 00:39:24,550
His hobbies are eating spicy chicken feet with Ha Na, making bets with Ha Na...

486
00:39:24,550 --> 00:39:28,730
- And with Ha Na...
- What is this? Everything best is about Unni Ha Na.

487
00:39:31,680 --> 00:39:36,320
I'm not really sure about this, but Won likes someone who won't leave him.

488
00:39:36,320 --> 00:39:40,700
I think he likes a girl whom he can take care of and protect.

489
00:39:41,420 --> 00:39:44,760
Originally, Won's dream was to be a movie director.

490
00:39:44,760 --> 00:39:49,330
But seeing as he threw away that dream, it seems he thought he had to compromise with reality...

491
00:39:49,330 --> 00:39:51,270
He must have thought about that himself.

492
00:39:51,270 --> 00:39:54,610
Oh, so his original dream was to be a movie director.

493
00:39:54,610 --> 00:39:59,630
We'll stop here for today. Whether there will be a next time depends on how you act.

494
00:40:06,690 --> 00:40:09,490
I'll treat you well from now on.

495
00:40:09,490 --> 00:40:13,370
Like a girl who won't ever leave.

496
00:41:01,370 --> 00:41:03,290
Seo Hoo.

497
00:41:06,120 --> 00:41:08,060
You missed me, haven't you?

498
00:41:10,610 --> 00:41:12,150
Let's go out.

499
00:41:12,150 --> 00:41:17,280
I can't. I have a lot of work left to do.

500
00:41:18,940 --> 00:41:22,200
I told them I'll listen to Team Leader Oh's opinion.

501
00:41:22,200 --> 00:41:25,600
The staff for the recital, and I especially,

502
00:41:25,600 --> 00:41:30,040
need clothes and shoes.

503
00:41:40,580 --> 00:41:42,620
- Let's go.
- Wait a minute.

504
00:41:44,510 --> 00:41:46,230
Seo Hoo.

505
00:41:53,980 --> 00:41:57,460
You've gotten prettier Oh Ha Na and skinnier.

506
00:41:57,460 --> 00:42:00,380
I feel unpleasant about this. You suddenly appear in front of me at work and—

507
00:42:00,380 --> 00:42:01,780
You've lost weight, haven't you?

508
00:42:01,780 --> 00:42:03,620
Cha Seo Hoo.

